With two days to go to the State Of The Nation Address, President Cyril Ramaphosa seems to be in good spirits. CAPE TOWN - With two days to go to the State of the Nation Address, President Cyril Ramaphosa seems to be in good spirits. He interacted with residents in Salt River, Cape Town, and even posed for some selfies. The president visited a local fish and chips eatery in the area. Ramaphosa says despite the challenges within the ANC, the people of South Africa come first. "When I speak on Thursday IÂ will be speaking to all South Africans," he said. "Let us focus on the message that we're going to put forward to South Africans."